{{Infobox journal | title = Mechademia | cover = Mechademia.jpg | discipline = [[Media studies]] | editor = Frenchy Lunning | publisher = [[University of Minnesota Press]] | country = United States | abbreviation = Mechademia | history = 2006-present | frequency = Annually | website = http://www.mechademia.org/ | link1 = https://muse.jhu.edu/journal/461 | link1-name = Online access at [[Project MUSE]] | link2 = https://muse.jhu.edu/journal/461 | link2-name = Online archives at Project MUSE | ISSN = 1934-2489 | eISSN = 2152-6648 | OCLC = 72523390 | LCCN = 2006215646 }} '''''Mechademia: An Annual Forum for Anime, Manga, and the Fan Arts''''' is an annual [[peer-reviewed]] [[academic journal]] in English about [[Japanese popular culture]] products and fan practices. It is published by the [[University of Minnesota Press]] and the [[editor-in-chief]] is [[Frenchy Lunning]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/feature/2005-01-26/5 |title=2004 Year in Review Anime/Manga Academic Highlights |last=Koulikov |first=Mikhail |date=January 26, 2005 |publisher=[[Anime News Network]] |accessdate=2009-05-16}}</ref> Mechademia has been an annual conference since 2001.<ref>{{cite web|title=Mechademia {{!}} Minneapolis College of Art and Design|url=http://mcad.edu/event/mechademia|website=mcad.edu}}</ref>
==Volumes== Since 2006, ten volumes have been published.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.upress.umn.edu/book-division/series/mechademia|title=Mechademia|work=Minnesota Press|accessdate=August 11, 2017}}</ref> Each volume is dedicated to a collection of articles themed around a specific topic, such as [[shojo manga]] or [[otaku|anime and manga fandom]]. It is indexed in [[Project MUSE]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://muse.jhu.edu/journal/461|title=Mechademia Vol. 1 (2006) through current issue|work=Project Muse|accessdate=August 11, 2017}}</ref> and [[JSTOR]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.jstor.org/journal/mech|title=Mechademia|work=Jstor|accessdate=August 11, 2017}}</ref> After a break of three years, a new series of Mechademia volumes will be published beginning in 2018, the first being themed around childhood. The scope of Mechademia will be broadened to include all of Asia in its remit.<ref>{{cite web|title=Call for Papers - Mechademia|url=http://www.mechademia.net/journal/call-for-papers/|website=www.mechademia.net|accessdate=9 August 2017}}</ref> {{Graphic novel list/header | OneLanguage = yes | Width = 72% | WithTitle = yes }} {{Graphic novel list | VolumeNumber = 1 | RelDate = December 22, 2006<ref>{{cite book|title=Mechademia 1: Emerging Worlds of Anime and Manga|isbn=0816649456|url=http://www.upress.umn.edu/book-division/books/mechademia-1|publisher=[[University of Minnesota Press]]|editor=Frenchy Lunning|accessdate=December 8, 2014}}</ref> | ISBN = 978-0-8166-4945-7 | Title = Mechademia 1: Emerging Worlds of Anime and Manga }}
