{{coord|48|44|56|N|135|38|46|E|display=title}} [[File:Петроглифы Сикачи-Аляна 4.JPG|thumb|[[Petroglyph]]]] '''Sikachi-Alyan''' is a small [[Nani people|Nanai]] village on the bank of the [[Amur River|Amur]] river located 75&nbsp;km north of [[Khabarovsk]]. The place is famous for its neolithic [[Petroglyphs of Sikachi-Alyan|petroglyph]]s (masks) carved on the surface of basalt stones. The drawings date back to the 13th century BC. The local findings demonstrate the ancient history of this area. There is a museum and an open-air reconstruction of an ancient village.<ref>[http://gov.khabkrai.ru/invest2.nsf/pages/petroglyphs_ru.htm Server of Khabarovsk Krai government (ru)] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120320171157/http://gov.khabkrai.ru/invest2.nsf/pages/petroglyphs_ru.htm |date=2012-03-20 }}</ref> [[File:Sikachi-Alyan birdview.jpg|thumb|center|400px|Sikachi-Alyan birdview]]
