{{Infobox journal | title = Studies in American Indian Literatures | cover = | former_names = Newsletter of the Association for the Study of American Indian Literatures, ASAIL Newsletter | abbreviation = Stud. Am. Indian Lit. | discipline = [[Native American studies]] | editor = Chadwick Allen | publisher = [[University of Nebraska Press]] on behalf of the [[Association for the Study of American Indian Literatures]] | country = United States | history = 1977-present | frequency = Quarterly | openaccess = | license = | ISSN = 0730-3238 | eISSN = 1548-9590 | CODEN = | JSTOR = 07303238 | LCCN = sf94091831 | OCLC = 54533161 | website = http://asail.org/sail-publications/sail-journal/ | link1 = http://www.nebraskapress.unl.edu/product/Studies-in-American-Indian-Literatures,673235.aspx | link1-name = Journal page at publisher's website | link2 = http://muse.jhu.edu/journals/studies_in_american_indian_literatures/ | link2-name = Online access at [[Project MUSE]] }} '''''Studies in American Indian Literatures''''' is a quarterly [[peer-reviewed]] [[academic journal]] covering [[Native American literature]]. It is published by the [[University of Nebraska Press]] on behalf of the [[Association for the Study of American Indian Literatures]].<ref name="SAIL">{{cite web |title=SAIL Publications |url=http://asail.org/sail-publications/ |publisher=Association for the Study of American Indian Literatures |accessdate=2015-03-13}}</ref><ref name="UNP">{{cite web |url=http://www.nebraskapress.unl.edu/product/Studies-in-American-Indian-Literatures,673235.aspx |title=Studies in American Indian Literatures |work=[[University of Nebraska Press]] |publisher=University of Nebraska |accessdate=2015-03-24}}</ref>
== History == The journal was established in 1977 as the ''Newsletter of the Association for the Study of American Indian Literatures'' and changed to ''ASAIL Newsletter'' in 1978 before the journal obtained its current title in 1980. Publication was interrupted from 1987 to 1989.<ref name="SAIL"/>
== Abstracting and indexing == The journal is abstracted and indexed in the [[Arts and Humanities Citation Index]],<ref name=ISI>{{cite web |url=http://ip-science.thomsonreuters.com/mjl/ |title=Master Journal List |publisher=[[Thomson Reuters]] |work=Intellectual Property & Science |accessdate=2015-03-26}}</ref> [[Current Contents]]/Arts & Humanities,<ref name=ISI/> and [[Scopus]].<ref name=Scopus>{{cite web |url=http://www.elsevier.com/online-tools/scopus/content-overview |title=Content overview |publisher=[[Elsevier]] |work=Scopus |accessdate=2015-03-26}}</ref>
